AUDIO: 'AI image models are incredible at giving you something new every time you prompt them, but that\'s also their biggest weakness. You see, the moment you need to make the same thing twice, the same character, the same product, your own face, it starts to get distorted and lose the details. But the good news is'

[00:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that you don\'t have to sit around waiting for some company to fix it, because you can train your own AI image model that locks onto exactly what you want and recreates it perfectly every single time. Now, you might be wondering, why can\'t I just use Nanao'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Banana Pro and give it a reference image instead? Well, a reference image only knows that one photo. A new angle, a new pose, different lighting, and it starts guessing, which is exactly where those details fall apart. And that\'s where in'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
